{
  "doc_id": "53752",
  "text": "The distinction between distributional and transdistributional properties extends to continuous time queuing models, where it can be shown that average response times are distributional while response time percentiles are trans-distributional [CITATION_1] . This has important implications for datacenters that provide services to clients in both conventional and cloud-based environments: service level agreements (SLAs) specified in terms of response time percentiles are inherently riskier than service level agreements based on average response time.",
  "correct_citation": {
